New Records: Liam Walker now holds the all-time goal record for Gibraltar with six goals
Key Match Events: Gibraltar ended a 713-day goal drought with Liam Walker's Olimpico goal
Walker missed a penalty to retake the lead for Gibraltar
James Scanlon scored Gibraltar's second goal in the 97th minute
Nicolas Hasler scored a penalty for Liechtenstein in the 104th minute
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match finished 2-2 between Gibraltar and Liechtenstein in the UEFA Nations League
